<TITLE> Half-day hartal held in Langadu to protest army camp withdrawal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangamati, August 16 (bdnews24.com)A half-day hartal was observed in Langadu Upazila in Rangamati hill district on Sunday, protesting army pullout from the Chittagong Hill Tracts Parbottya Shamo Odhikar Andolan (PSOA) and Parbottya Bangalee Chhatra Parishad (PBCP) called the half-day closure, reports Satrang Chakma, bdnews24.com correspondent from Rangamati. The protest was observed from 6am to noon throughout the upazila. All business centres including shops and educational institutions remained closed. Protestors marched through the upazila headquarters in processions through the hartal period. No untoward incident was reported. Md Alamgir Kabir, PBCP central committee president said his organisation, after a meeting at Bahaddarhat in Chittagong on Friday, was also declaring a 12-hour roadblock on August 20 to be imposed through the three hill districts on Rangamati, Khagrhachharhi and Bandarban. The meeting was attended by PBCP leaders of Rangamati, Khagrhachharhi, Bandarban, Chittagong metropolitan and Chittagong University units, who demand a stop to further army pullout in the region. bdne
